        "$:/plugins/ihm/bible/macros/bq": {
            "text": "\\define bqb(book,verse, bible)\n<div class=\"bqb-div\" title=<<bverse \"$book$\" \"$verse$\" \"$bible$\"  \"tip\">>>\n<span  style=\"color: #aeb0b5; font-size: 1.4em; vertical-align:bottom;\">&ldquo;</span>\n<span class=\"bqb-quote\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\">\n//<<bverse \"$book$\" \"$verse$\" \"$bible$\" \"text\" >>//\n</span>\n<span style=\"color: #aeb0b5; font-size: 1.4em; vertical-align:bottom;\">&rdquo;</span>\n<br>\n<span class=\"bqb-ref\">---<<bverse \"$book$\" \"$verse$\" \"$bible$\"  \"refshort\" >></span>\n</div>\n\\end\n\n\\define bqi(book,verse, bible,nums)\n<span title=<<bverse \"$book$\" \"$verse$\" \"$bible$\" \"tip\">>>\n  <span class=\"bqi-quote\">\n  //<<bverse \"$book$\" \"$verse$\"  \"$bible$\" \"inline-text\">>//\n  </span>\n<span class=\"bqi-ref\">(<<bverse \"$book$\" \"$verse$\" \"$bible$\"  \"refshorter\">>)</span>\n</span>\n\\end\n\n\nThis is a great test, many of the names stood out, and I found it very familiar, <<bqi Gen 1,2>>, what is the relationship to them today? Are they okay? Yes, they are okay. Thay are my children.\n\n\n<<bqb Gen @1,1-2,1>>\n<<bqi Gen 1,1-2,1 VUL>>\n\n<<bqb Gen @1,29-2,3 MEX>>\n\n<$list filter=\"[[$:/plugins/ihm/bible/translations]indexes[]]\">\n{{!!title}} --- <$transclude tiddler=\"$:/plugins/ihm/bible/translations\" index={{!!title}} ></$transclude><br>\n</$list>\n\nGen 1,1: \n<$view tiddler= \"$:/plugins/ihm/bible/books/VUL/Gen\" index={{$:/plugins/ihm/bible/verse}} > </$view>\n\nsource:\n{{$:/plugins/ihm/bible/books/VUL/Gen##source}}\n\n",
